cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with two optimization problems, one related to graphs and the other related to geometric objects in the plane. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the use of graph theory and combinatorial optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem of finding minimum paths and barriers is a classic problem in game theory, which could place the paper in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of the problems, which could also place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
